# 3DAI Project Conventions

## Architecture

- Monorepo: `app/` (Electron), `services/api/`, `services/worker/`, `packages/shared/`, `infra/`
- Shared types live in `packages/shared/` — import from there, never duplicate type definitions
- Database schema is the source of truth at `infra/supabase/migrations/`
- Keep `packages/shared/src/schemas/database.ts` in sync with migration SQL

## TypeScript

- Strict mode always enabled
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow with type guards
- Use `const` by default, `let` only when reassignment is needed, never `var`
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use path aliases (`@shared/`, `@api/`, `@worker/`) instead of deep relative imports

## Naming

- Files: `kebab-case.ts` for modules, `PascalCase.tsx` for React components
- Variables/functions: `camelCase`
- Types/interfaces: `PascalCase`
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`
- Database columns: `snake_case` (matches Postgres convention)
- Enum-like unions: lowercase with underscores matching the DB enum values

## Error Handling

- Always handle errors explicitly — no empty catch blocks
- Use typed error classes that extend `Error` for domain errors
- Log errors with context (operation, entity ID, user ID) before rethrowing
